STATE OF CONNECTICUT v. JERMAINE PRINCE (14697)

Foti, Heiman and Schaller, Js.

Argued February 29 decision released March 26, 1996 Leonard M. Crone, for the appellant (defendant). Paul J. Ferencek, assistant state’s attorney, with whom, on the brief, were Frank S. Maco, state’s attorney, and Andrew M. Wittstein, supervisory assistant state’s attorney, for the appellee (state). PER CURIAM.

The judgment is affirmed.
